    schema1:description "Thomas Pelham-Holles, Duke of Newcastle, held major political office for nearly 4 decades, the ultimate insider of 18th-century British politics. He was both Secretary of State and First Lord of the Treasury. Although a member of the House of Lords, he exerted considerable influence in the Commons as the patron of several boroughs."@en ;
